	abstract = {OBJECTIVE: Cerebral small vessel disease (SVD) is considered the most important vascular contributor to cognitive decline and dementia, although a causal relation between its MRI markers and dementia still needs to be established. The authors investigated the relation between baseline SVD severity as well as SVD progression on MRI markers and incident dementia, by subtype, in individuals with sporadic SVD over a follow-up period of 14 years.
