RESULTS: When using all the input features, the algorithm predicted VT values with high accuracy (87.8 ± 8.3\%) for both lesion and non-lesion voxels. The SHAP values demonstrated high impact of the late PET frames (60-70, 70-80, and 80-90 min p.i.) and plasma activity concentrations on the VT prediction, while the influence of the ASL-derived perfusion, voxel coordinates, and the lesion mask was low. Among all the combinations of the late PET frames and plasma activity concentrations, the 70-80 min p.i. frame divided by the 30 min p.i. plasma sample produced the closest VT estimate in the ischemic lesion.
