RESULTS: Before harmonization, significant differences in FA and MD were observed between matched controls of different sites (p {\textless} 0.05). After harmonization these site-differences were removed. Within each site, RISH harmonization did not alter the effect sizes of FA, MD and PSMD between patients and controls (relative change in Cohen's d = 4 \%) nor the strength of association with WMH volume (relative change in R2 = 2.8 \%). After harmonization, patient data of all sites could be aggregated in a single analysis to infer the association between WMH volume and FA (R2 = 0.62), MD (R2 = 0.64), and PSMD (R2 = 0.60).
